   "source": [
    "# Notebook 2: Multiplicative Depth Budget Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Before writing a single line of FHE code, you need to know:\n",
    "1. How many multiplicative levels does your ViT consume?\n",
    "2. What CKKS parameters do you need?\n",
    "3. What is the memory and latency cost?\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook walks through the depth budget for a 6-layer ViT."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, '../')\n",
    "from utils.depth_counter import vit_depth_budget, print_depth_report\n",
    "import pandas as pd"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Depth Budget Comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "Compare three ViT configurations:\n",
    "1. **Vanilla ViT** — softmax, LayerNorm, GELU-4 (smallest polynomial)\n",
    "2. **BOLT-style** — linear attention, no LayerNorm, GELU-4\n",
    "3. **Iron-style** — softmax approx, LayerNorm approx, GELU-27"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print_depth_report()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Detailed breakdown for BOLT-style (our target)\n",
    "result = vit_depth_budget(\n",
    "    n_layers=6,\n",
    "    gelu_degree=4,\n",
    "    attention_type='linear',\n",
    "    layernorm_type='removed'\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"BOLT-style ViT-S (6 layers) Depth Breakdown\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 50)\n",
    "for k, v in result['per_block'].items():\n",
    "    if 'total' not in k or k == 'block_total':\n",
    "        print(f\"  {k:<30} {v:>4} levels\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(f\"  {'Patch embedding':<30} {result['patch_embedding']:>4} levels\")\n",
    "print(f\"  {'All {n} blocks × {block}':<30} {result['all_blocks_total']:>4} levels\".format(\n",
    "    n=result['n_layers'], block=result['per_block']['block_total']))\n",
    "print(f\"  {'Classification head':<30} {result['classification_head']:>4} levels\")\n",
    "print(f\"  {'─'*35}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  {'TOTAL':<30} {result['grand_total']:>4} levels\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## CKKS Parameter Selection\n",
    "\n",
    "Given the required depth, what polynomial degree $n$ do we need for 128-bit security?\n",
    "\n",
    "Reference: [HomomorphicEncryption.org Standard](https://homomorphicencryption.org/standard/)\n",
    "\n",
    "| $n$ | Max $\\log_2(q)$ | Security |\n",
    "|-----|---------------|----------|\n",
    "| $2^{13}$ | 218 | 128-bit |\n",
    "| $2^{14}$ | 438 | 128-bit |\n",
    "| $2^{15}$ | 881 | 128-bit |\n",
    "| $2^{16}$ | 1761 | 128-bit |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# For BOLT-style with depth=50, scale=40 bits:\n",
    "# q = 60 + 50*40 + 60 = 2120 bits\n",
    "# This exceeds n=2^15 (max 881 bits)!\n",
    "# Need n=2^16 for 128-bit security, or reduce depth.\n",
    "\n",
    "def required_ring_size(depth, scale_bits=40, security=128):\n",
    "    q_bits = 60 + depth * scale_bits + 60\n",
    "    limits_128 = {8192: 218, 16384: 438, 32768: 881, 65536: 1761}\n",
    "    for n, max_q in sorted(limits_128.items()):\n",
    "        if q_bits <= max_q:\n",
    "            return n, q_bits\n",
    "    return None, q_bits\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Required ring size for different depth targets\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 50)\n",
    "for depth in [10, 20, 30, 40, 50, 60]:\n",
    "    n, q_bits = required_ring_size(depth)\n",
    "    n_str = f\"2^{int(n).bit_length()-1}\" if n else \"INFEASIBLE\"\n",
    "    slots = n // 2 if n else 0\n",
    "    print(f\"  Depth {depth:2d}: q={q_bits:4d} bits → n={n_str:<8} ({slots} slots)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Key Insight\n",
    "\n",
    "Reducing depth from 50 → 30 lets us use $n=2^{15}$ instead of $n=2^{16}$.\n",
    "This is a **4× speedup** (FHE operations scale as $O(n \\log n)$).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Research question**: Can we design a 6-layer ViT that achieves >85% on CIFAR-10 with depth ≤ 30?"
   ]
  }
